'''Ahmed Chami''' sometimes '''Ahmed Reda Chami''' ({{lang-ar|أحمد الشامي}} &ndash; born 16 May 1961, [[Casablanca]]) is a Moroccan politician of the [[Socialist Union of Popular Forces]]. Between 2007 and 2012, he held the position of Minister of Industry, Trade and New Technologies in the [[Cabinet of Morocco|cabinet]] of [[Abbas El Fassi]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Nadia DREF|title=Ahmed Chami primé|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lematin/2816|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Le Matin|date=2007-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Le plan de bataille d'Ahmed Chami|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/letemps/18649|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Le temps|date=2009-12-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Ahmed Réda Chami : Cartésien…pragmatique|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lagazette/19056|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=La Gazette du Maroc|date=2009-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Investissement : Hassan Bernoussi sous la coupe de Ahmed Chami|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/challenge/124|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Challenge hebdo|date=2007-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Imane Bouhrara|title=Ahmed Reda Chami, un ministre branché Net|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/financesnews/7042|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Finances news|date=2010-02-04}}</ref>
