'''Godfrey Box''' was a 16th-century [[United Kingdom|British]] entrepreneur. An immigrant from the [[Low Countries]], he built [[England]]'s first iron-splitting mill on the [[River Darent]] at Dartford Creek in [[Dartford]], [[Kent]], some time between 1590 and 1595.

